 research attention. The Italian Welfare State in a European Perspective is the first book to explore the evolution of Italy's welfare state in the decades since the ‘Trente Glorieuses’ (1945–75). It offers a rare overview and analysis of the Italian situation based on an in-depth study of the main social policy fields (including education, higher education and taxation policies), a detailed analysis of the connection between policies and their outputs/outcomes and a comparative perspective framing the Italian case within the European context. This is the first English-language book to take a comparative look at the Italian welfare state as a whole since the 2008 economic crisis, It will be a valuable resource for academics and researchers, as well as students.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aPublic welfarezItaly. 0aWelfare statezItaly. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Social Policy.2bisacsh1 aAgostini, Chiara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAlbertini, Marco, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAscoli, Ugo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAscoli, Ugo, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBaldini, Massimo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBallarino, Gabriele, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGuerra, Maria Cecilia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKazepov, Yuri, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMigliavacca, Mauro, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNatali, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPavolini, Emmanuele, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/c